15:48.030 --> 15:49.615
Yeah, no, let's talk on Friday.

15:50.407 --> 15:52.785
Uh... um...

15:52.868 --> 15:55.287
Marie, um... eh, don't tell me.

15:55.371 --> 15:57.539
- Adler.
- Adler. I told you not to tell me.

15:57.623 --> 15:58.958
What brings you around here?

15:59.041 --> 16:02.294
Wait. Oh, shoot. Walk with me.

16:03.295 --> 16:04.421
No offense, Marie,

16:04.505 --> 16:06.505
but I was hoping never to see you again.
What's up?

16:06.548 --> 16:08.342
Oh, I need a lawyer.

16:08.926 --> 16:10.594
Uh-oh. What happened?

16:10.678 --> 16:12.238
No, no, no, I'm not the one in trouble.

16:12.262 --> 16:14.765
I just need to press charges
against someone else.

16:14.848 --> 16:17.184
Oh, well, I'm not...
I'm not that kind of lawyer.

16:17.267 --> 16:20.479
Well, I know, but I... I thought
you might know someone who was.

16:21.146 --> 16:22.898
Well, who do you want to sue?

16:23.315 --> 16:26.360
Pretty much everybody,
but I thought I'd start with the City.

16:29.071 --> 16:31.615
The same... you got the same number?

16:31.699 --> 16:32.699
Yeah.

16:33.534 --> 16:34.743
I'll get you a name.

16:43.335 --> 16:45.671
Yeah, Don and I
went to law school together.

16:46.296 --> 16:48.650
Spent more time on the basketball court
than in the library,

16:48.674 --> 16:50.509
but somehow it worked out.

16:50.592 --> 16:52.803
Uh, water, coffee?

16:54.346 --> 16:56.140
Oh, uh, no, thanks.

16:57.057 --> 17:00.310
So, he sent me
your case file, which...

17:03.272 --> 17:04.857
By the way, let me just say,

17:04.940 --> 17:08.861
what happened to you should not happen
to anyone, ever.

17:11.238 --> 17:12.448
Yeah, well.

17:13.198 --> 17:15.784
You know, no one ever accuses
a robbery victim of lying

17:15.867 --> 17:17.911
or someone who says he was carjacked.

17:17.994 --> 17:18.994
Doesn't happen.

17:20.039 --> 17:21.957
But when it comes to sexual assault...

17:26.170 --> 17:27.296
Anyway, have a seat.

17:29.798 --> 17:32.384
So, Don told me about the check
they gave you.

17:32.468 --> 17:33.886
Reimbursement for your fine.

17:34.636 --> 17:35.763
How do you feel about that?

17:35.846 --> 17:41.643
Well, at first, I was like, "$500, cool."

17:43.270 --> 17:49.026
But then I got to thinking that there were
other things that I lost because of this.

17:50.360 --> 17:52.780
Like... my job,

17:53.614 --> 17:54.615
my housing,

17:55.699 --> 17:56.992
free counselors.

17:58.285 --> 18:01.371
Plus, you know... friendships.

18:02.372 --> 18:06.710
And I know, it's, like, "Hey,
$500 that you didn't have yesterday,"

18:06.794 --> 18:09.797
but my whole life, I've just been, like,

18:10.589 --> 18:15.094
"Take what you get,
and just be happy that it's not worse."

18:18.180 --> 18:20.682
But something about this
made me feel like...

18:24.812 --> 18:26.772
maybe that's not good enough this time.

18:28.816 --> 18:31.318
You know what happens when you decide
you're not gonna just

18:31.610 --> 18:32.945
take what you get anymore?

18:34.029 --> 18:35.029
What?

18:36.448 --> 18:37.533
You get more.

18:41.286 --> 18:43.765
- Okay, so I spoke to our victims.
- Hello to you too, Detective.

18:43.789 --> 18:46.601
Oh, hey, uh,...they're
okay with you dropping kidnapping

18:46.625 --> 18:48.144
- and not going to trial...
- Excellent.

18:48.168 --> 18:50.480
...as long as they can address the court
at his sentencing.

18:50.504 --> 18:52.232
They wanna look him in the eye.

18:52.256 --> 18:54.633
Yeah, sure, of course.
I gotta take this, thanks.

18:54.716 --> 18:58.011
- Hang on. What about the password?
- Oh, yeah. No, he won't give it up.

18:58.095 --> 19:01.095
What do you mean? He's a fucking rapist.
How about he doesn't have a choice?

19:01.723 --> 19:03.767
- What should I do? Waterboard him?
- Can you?

19:04.351 --> 19:06.663
Just tell him, if he doesn't cough it up,
you're goin' to trial,

19:06.687 --> 19:07.727
kidnapping and everything.

19:07.771 --> 19:11.066
I have a serial rapist who's pleading
guilty to 30 counts of sexual assault.

19:11.525 --> 19:13.245
Okay? I'm not gonna blow this
on a password.

19:13.277 --> 19:15.863
- Gonzalez. Ah, shit.
- There are other women on there.

19:16.196 --> 19:18.116
Don't you wanna know who they are,
what happened?

19:18.157 --> 19:20.742
Yes, but I'm not gonna risk going to trial
with this guy. Okay?

19:20.826 --> 19:22.161
See you at the sentencing.

19:39.720 --> 19:40.720
You good?

19:41.221 --> 19:42.221
Yeah.

20:28.143 --> 20:29.311
You okay?

20:43.617 --> 20:44.826
Hey, there she is.

20:45.369 --> 20:46.369
Come on in.

20:52.960 --> 20:54.336
<i>I have nightmares.</i>

20:55.587 --> 20:59.549
I am scared... all of the time.

20:59.633 --> 21:00.968
Every minute of every day.

21:01.051 --> 21:05.847
My friends try to help me,
but I have a hard time trusting people.

21:06.556 --> 21:08.225
Uh, I can't sleep.

21:08.517 --> 21:09.726
I'm in pain.

21:12.813 --> 21:13.939
I've lost weight.

21:14.022 --> 21:16.566
I've lost work. I've lost money.

21:18.860 --> 21:20.279
I have violent thoughts.

21:20.737 --> 21:22.990
I've never had violent thoughts before,
ever.

21:23.949 --> 21:26.243
You think it's just one night.

21:26.326 --> 21:28.370
Compared to all of the other minutes
of my life,

21:28.453 --> 21:31.623
how could this one short incident
make a difference? But...

21:34.293 --> 21:35.419
it does.

21:37.629 --> 21:43.051
Your Honor, what I really want to do
is I wanna ask the defendant a question.

21:43.135 --> 21:44.219
Can I do that?

21:44.594 --> 21:45.679
By all means.

21:49.975 --> 21:51.351
Why did you pick me?

21:52.561 --> 21:55.856
What was I doing
that made you wanna come for me?

21:55.939 --> 21:58.358
I'm so scared of doing it again.

21:58.442 --> 22:03.113
I don't water my lawn anymore.
I... I don't read by the window.

22:04.990 --> 22:07.200
They say that routines
make you vulnerable,

22:07.284 --> 22:10.078
so anything routine, I just stopped doing.

22:12.664 --> 22:15.292
It's made my world very small,

22:15.375 --> 22:17.502
and I still don't feel safe.

22:17.961 --> 22:20.589
I think if I just knew what it was,
what I did.

22:22.174 --> 22:25.385
If I knew what that one thing was,
then I'd stop doing it

22:25.469 --> 22:27.721
and then maybe
I could get my life back again.

22:30.057 --> 22:33.977
Your Honor,
Mr. McCarthy has other victims,

22:34.603 --> 22:37.856
ones who weren't up to being here today
and seeing him.

22:39.191 --> 22:42.152
They want to be sure you don't misread
their absence as indifference

22:42.444 --> 22:45.197
'cause they care about
what is happening here today

22:45.280 --> 22:46.740
more than you can imagine.

22:48.367 --> 22:51.286
If at any point
in the near or distant future,

22:51.370 --> 22:53.121
Mr. McCarthy is a free man,

22:53.663 --> 22:55.874
they will not feel safe...

22:56.625 --> 22:57.625
ever.

22:58.627 --> 23:00.504
And these women deserve to feel safe.

23:03.882 --> 23:05.926
Bottom line is
they don't want to go to trial,

23:06.009 --> 23:07.302
which is good.

23:08.136 --> 23:09.136
Neither do we.

23:10.138 --> 23:10.972
Why not?

23:11.056 --> 23:14.101
Because they will try to make you look
as bad as they do.

23:15.852 --> 23:18.897
They already did that once,
let's not give them another swing at it.

23:21.566 --> 23:24.861
So, everyone wants a settlement,
the question is how much.

23:26.238 --> 23:27.489
We have an offer.

23:28.740 --> 23:30.659
