26:29.254 --> 26:30.297
"Listen, motherfucker,

26:30.380 --> 26:33.425
you let all this horrible shit go down
day after day after day.

26:33.508 --> 26:37.220
Is it too much to ask on this one day,
you get one fucking thing right"?

26:37.304 --> 26:38.888
And look, it worked.

26:40.807 --> 26:42.642
- Hey, did you tell her yet?
- Tell me what?

26:42.726 --> 26:44.269
This is it. Right here.

26:44.728 --> 26:46.313
We don't need to get into this.

26:46.396 --> 26:48.982
What do you mean?
What don't we, uh, need to get into?

26:49.065 --> 26:51.318
This is the exact spot
where Max the Knife was born.

26:51.401 --> 26:52.694
Who?

26:52.777 --> 26:54.696
His alter ego. Come on, tell her.

26:54.779 --> 26:57.741
- I have no idea what you're talking about.
- Oh, come on.

26:58.325 --> 27:03.163
- I gotta take a piss.
- Oh, no! What? Come on, tell me.

27:05.498 --> 27:06.541
I don't like that.

27:06.625 --> 27:09.628
Uh, that is because you have a problem
with control.

27:09.711 --> 27:12.380
Oh, I have a problem with control.

27:12.964 --> 27:14.507
- Wow, me.
- Yeah.

27:14.591 --> 27:17.052
If you don't have every little piece
of information...

27:17.135 --> 27:19.346
if you don't make
all the decisions yourself... whoa.

27:19.429 --> 27:22.682
- So, I'm sorry, can you hear this?
- Whatever it is, I agree with Grace.

27:22.766 --> 27:25.393
I'm just saying,
if you could loosen up a little...

27:25.477 --> 27:32.275
Oh, please, you are, like, the least
loose loose person I have ever met.

27:32.567 --> 27:34.277
You're, like, faux-loose.

27:34.569 --> 27:36.696
- Are you kidding me?
- No.

27:36.988 --> 27:37.989
Mmm.

27:38.198 --> 27:40.241
<i>♪ Oh, the shark, babe ♪</i>

27:40.950 --> 27:43.036
<i>♪ Has such teeth, dear ♪</i>

27:44.162 --> 27:48.166
<i>♪ And it shows they're a pearly white... ♪</i>

27:48.625 --> 27:49.668
What is he doing?

27:50.335 --> 27:54.839
<i>♪ Just a jackknife
Has old MacHeath, babe... ♪</i>

27:54.923 --> 27:57.550
Oh, no!

27:58.385 --> 27:59.844
<i>♪ Oh, out of sight... ♪</i>

28:00.178 --> 28:03.765
This is where it comes from?
He has done this before?

28:03.848 --> 28:06.976
Every time we go out.
It's kind of his thing.

28:07.435 --> 28:11.898
<i>♪ Scarlet billows start to spread ♪</i>

28:13.400 --> 28:17.862
Is it so bad that it's kind of adorable?

28:19.030 --> 28:21.324
- Or... or is it just bad?
- Yeah, I would say the latter.

28:21.408 --> 28:23.243
Oh, no!

28:24.786 --> 28:26.413
<i>♪ On the sidewalk... ♪</i>

28:28.665 --> 28:32.127
- Good evening, Detectives.
- Oh, Taggart. This is my guy, Steve.

28:32.252 --> 28:33.253
- Evening.
- Hey.

28:34.170 --> 28:37.257
Uh, interesting update.
Chris McCarthy's lawyer called,

28:37.340 --> 28:38.967
says he wants to be interviewed.

28:39.259 --> 28:41.428
Says he wants to explain himself.

28:41.511 --> 28:43.596
He thinks it could be helpful
to law enforcement.

28:43.680 --> 28:47.058
- Are you serious? We get to talk to him?
- No, not you, just me.

28:47.892 --> 28:51.062
Believe it or not,
women make him uncomfortable.

28:57.527 --> 29:00.405
<i>Well, the problem is
you're always a step behind.</i>

29:01.406 --> 29:02.449
<i>You're reacting.</i>

29:05.452 --> 29:07.954
<i>You wanna catch guys like me,
you gotta get out ahead of us.</i>

29:08.037 --> 29:12.208
<i>Anticipate,
because we think about this a lot.</i>

29:13.376 --> 29:14.376
<i>And we're smart.</i>

29:15.211 --> 29:16.291
<i>Smart how?</i>

29:16.337 --> 29:18.590
<i>Careful with prints. Careful with DNA.</i>

29:18.673 --> 29:21.676
<i>It's like being out in the wilderness.
Leave no trace.</i>

29:21.760 --> 29:23.760
<i>It's easier to catch guys like you</i>

29:23.803 --> 29:24.822
<i>when they're just starting out.</i>

29:24.846 --> 29:28.558
<i>Well, it's like anything. You know,
the more you do it, the better you get.</i>

29:30.935 --> 29:32.937
<i>That first one, up in Washington?</i>

29:33.897 --> 29:37.192
<i>I left... all kinds of stuff behind.</i>

29:37.275 --> 29:38.275
<i>Hair, fluids.</i>

29:38.943 --> 29:42.447
<i>All I could think about was all that DNA,
you know, all over the place.</i>

29:43.740 --> 29:46.159
<i>All they had to do was compare it
to my military records.</i>

29:46.242 --> 29:49.996
<i>I was dead sure they were gonna knock
on my door the next day and take me away.</i>

29:50.705 --> 29:51.790
<i>But nothing happened.</i>

29:53.166 --> 29:54.167
<i>And so you think...</i>

29:55.418 --> 29:56.418
<i>"Okay.</i>

29:57.921 --> 29:59.672
<i>Cool, I guess I can do this."</i>

30:06.387 --> 30:08.223
Hey, we got the guy.

30:13.269 --> 30:14.437
Okay.

30:15.230 --> 30:16.231
What is it?

30:18.691 --> 30:19.818
You know...

30:20.860 --> 30:25.073
...it's all the other sociopaths out there
with their rape kits and their guns,

30:25.156 --> 30:29.285
thinking... "Hey, I guess I can do this."

30:30.203 --> 30:31.203
You can't do that.

30:31.830 --> 30:34.082
You can't take on
all the bad guys at once.

30:35.041 --> 30:38.545
We did a good thing getting this guy.
Let it be a good thing.

30:43.883 --> 30:48.012
You got the job done.
Cheer the fuck up. God!

30:50.390 --> 30:51.391
Okay.

30:51.933 --> 30:52.933
Yes!

30:55.979 --> 30:58.898
- "One day's burden is enough for one day."
- Exactly.

30:58.982 --> 31:01.568
"One day's burden is enough for one day."
I like that.

31:02.026 --> 31:03.027
It's from the <i>Bible.</i>

31:03.945 --> 31:06.489
- Shut up.
- Matthew 6:34.

31:06.823 --> 31:07.991
Whatever that means.

31:12.996 --> 31:14.581
<i>Do you feel remorse?</i>

31:15.123 --> 31:17.876
<i>I mean,
I know I can't be out there.</i>

31:18.793 --> 31:20.295
<i>I wasn't ever gonna stop.</i>

31:32.390 --> 31:34.267
Congratulations, hon,
drive carefully.

31:34.350 --> 31:35.184
Thank you.

31:35.268 --> 31:37.329
- You can just pay the clerk at window C.
- Thank you.

31:37.353 --> 31:39.105
- Yes, sir, how can I help you?
- Hi...

31:41.983 --> 31:43.151
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

31:43.234 --> 31:44.986
Could you take my picture for me?

31:45.236 --> 31:46.236
Sure.

31:57.415 --> 31:58.415
There you go.

32:01.127 --> 32:02.629
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

33:04.399 --> 33:05.399
Parker.

33:08.569 --> 33:09.570
Um...

33:11.322 --> 33:13.658
Yeah. Yes, send her up.

33:15.410 --> 33:16.577
Oh, okay.

33:18.496 --> 33:19.914
I'll come down.

33:37.890 --> 33:39.308
Marie, hi.

33:42.186 --> 33:44.939
Uh, do you want to go somewhere,
so we can talk?

33:45.023 --> 33:48.067
No. I don't really wanna
be alone with you.

33:48.484 --> 33:49.861
You understand that, right?

33:50.653 --> 33:51.653
I guess so.

33:52.613 --> 33:53.613
Yes.

33:54.115 --> 33:56.075
So, I got my $500 back.

33:57.076 --> 33:59.537
And I got more money from the City,
as you probably know.

33:59.620 --> 34:00.620
I do.

34:08.254 --> 34:09.714
You know what I never got...

34:11.549 --> 34:12.549
ever...

34:13.342 --> 34:14.385
from anybody?

34:16.429 --> 34:17.554
An apology.

34:20.016 --> 34:23.351
Even I know, when you mess up,
you apologize.

34:24.812 --> 34:26.313
And when you mess up so bad,

34:26.688 --> 34:28.649
when your one stupid mistake

34:28.733 --> 34:30.735
ruins a person's entire life,

34:31.069 --> 34:32.402
you apologize more.

34:32.487 --> 34:33.487
I'm sorry.

34:38.159 --> 34:40.453
I'm very, very sorry.

34:47.752 --> 34:48.795
Next time...

34:50.004 --> 34:51.005
do better.

34:54.217 --> 34:55.217
Okay.

35:13.736 --> 35:16.489
I was really hoping he would give up
that goddamn password.

35:16.572 --> 35:18.783
Jason said he'd keep at it
in his free time.

35:19.158 --> 35:21.369
- He has free time?
- Not really, no.

35:22.036 --> 35:23.036
Hey...

35:23.371 --> 35:24.413
um...

35:25.748 --> 35:26.999
Listen, before you go...

35:28.042 --> 35:31.295
- I just wanted to say...
- Oh, no, no, don't. Please.

35:31.963 --> 35:33.443
- Don't what?
- Do that thing, that...

35:33.756 --> 35:37.552
sincere "this has meant the world to me"
woman-bonding thing.

35:37.635 --> 35:41.013
No, I... I was not going to woman-bond.

35:41.097 --> 35:42.557
- Bullshit.
- No.

35:42.849 --> 35:45.601
No. I was just, uh, was just gonna say...

35:45.685 --> 35:46.685
What?

35:49.105 --> 35:52.108
Okay, fine you're right.
I was gonna woman-bond.

35:54.944 --> 35:56.112
Cut me some slack.

35:57.446 --> 35:58.739
I never had a mentor.

35:58.823 --> 36:00.199
I hate the word mentor.

36:02.493 --> 36:03.493
Fine...

36:04.412 --> 36:05.788
I won't say anything.

36:08.916 --> 36:09.917
Thank you.

37:02.428 --> 37:03.971
This is Detective Duvall.

37:06.599 --> 37:08.017
<i>Hi, um...</i>

37:09.352 --> 37:11.395
<i>I don't know if you know who I am, uh...</i>

37:12.605 --> 37:13.898
<i>this is Marie Adler.</i>

37:17.693 --> 37:18.903
Marie Adler.

37:20.238 --> 37:21.781
Of course I know who you are.

37:24.075 --> 37:26.155
<i>I hope it's okay that I'm calling.</i>

37:26.285 --> 37:28.371
I got your number from my lawyer.

37:30.915 --> 37:32.291
Yes, of course.

37:34.293 --> 37:35.293
How are you?

37:35.419 --> 37:39.131
I'm okay. I'm, uh...
I'm at the beach, actually.

37:41.884 --> 37:44.720
- Well, that sounds nice.
<i>- Yeah, it is.</i>

37:45.846 --> 37:46.846
Um...

37:47.640 --> 37:50.977
Hey, I just, um...
I... I was calling to say, uh...

37:52.478 --> 37:57.400
to... to thank you for, you know,
everything that you did.

38:01.112 --> 38:02.321
Well, of course.

38:04.907 --> 38:07.034
I'm... I'm so glad we were able to help.

38:07.702 --> 38:08.862
<i>You did...</i>

38:10.579 --> 38:11.579
totally.

38:15.251 --> 38:18.045
You know, the thing is,
I've spent my whole life...

38:18.838 --> 38:23.301
trying really hard to believe
that most people are basically good,

38:23.592 --> 38:25.469
<i>even when the ones I knew weren't.</i>

38:25.886 --> 38:27.513
I don't know, I guess it just...

38:30.349 --> 38:31.767
gave me hope or something.

38:32.059 --> 38:33.144
I can see that.

38:34.395 --> 38:37.815
<i>Then this thing happened. The rape and...</i>

38:38.274 --> 38:40.651
I don't know,
it just became harder for me to...

38:41.444 --> 38:44.780
believe that there was really any good
in the world.

38:44.864 --> 38:48.701
<i>And I think that that was the hardest part
of this whole thing.</i>

38:49.493 --> 38:51.203
<i>Waking up feeling hopeless.</i>

38:52.872 --> 38:54.874
And I would think things like, "Well...

38:58.002 --> 39:00.046
if the world is this bad, do I...

39:01.505 --> 39:03.924
do I even wanna be in it?"
You know?

39:08.262 --> 39:09.262
I do.

39:11.849 --> 39:13.934
<i>But then, out of nowhere,</i>

39:14.018 --> 39:15.978
<i>I hear about these two people</i>

39:16.354 --> 39:18.773
in some completely other part
of the country,

39:18.856 --> 39:21.692
looking out for me
and making things right.

39:21.776 --> 39:22.776
And...

39:24.570 --> 39:27.031
I don't know, more than...
more than anything else,

39:28.532 --> 39:30.242
more than him getting locked up...

39:32.244 --> 39:33.579
more than the money I got,

39:34.622 --> 39:35.956
it was hearing that,

39:37.541 --> 39:39.043
about you guys, that

39:39.126 --> 39:40.878
<i>just changed things completely.</i>

39:42.296 --> 39:44.090
<i>And I... I wake up now,</i>

39:44.173 --> 39:45.174
and...

39:48.594 --> 39:50.679
I can imagine good things happening.

39:56.394 --> 39:59.063
I'm... I'm so happy to hear that, Marie.

40:00.564 --> 40:02.566
So, anyway, I just...

40:04.777 --> 40:07.947
wanted you to know that you...
you did that for me...

40:11.325 --> 40:12.618
and to say thank you.

40:14.995 --> 40:15.996
You're welcome.

40:20.543 --> 40:21.877
Thank you for calling.

40:22.294 --> 40:23.629
Yeah, you bet.

40:27.508 --> 40:29.552
Uh, hey, you have a good day, okay?

40:30.928 --> 40:31.928
You too.

40:35.516 --> 40:36.516
Okay.

40:37.393 --> 40:38.393
Bye.

40:40.563 --> 40:41.563
Bye.

41:40.956 --> 41:43.375
<i>I got a call from someone
just now.</i>

41:44.001 --> 41:45.001
Yeah.

41:45.336 --> 41:46.504
Marie Adler.

41:48.547 --> 41:50.299
- Oh, my God.
<i>- Yeah.</i>

41:50.382 --> 41:53.469
- <i>What'd she say?
- She was calling from the beach.</i>

41:53.552 --> 41:57.389
<i>And she was calling to say
she's doing very well.</i>

41:57.681 --> 42:00.226
And that, uh, she wanted to say...

42:02.269 --> 42:03.312
<i>thank you.</i>

